# Why I’m Transitioning Into QA

## Background

I am currently transitioning into Software Quality Assurance. I became interested in QA while learning about how software is tested and how quality is maintained throughout development.

## Why QA

What attracts me to QA is the analytical aspect of the work: understanding how systems behave, identifying edge cases, and documenting issues clearly so they can be reproduced and fixed.

QA also requires structured thinking, attention to detail, and clear communication between technical and non-technical teams.

## What I’m Learning

My current focus areas include:

* Manual testing fundamentals
* Writing test cases
* Writing clear bug reports
* API testing
* Basic testing tools

## This Portfolio

This repository is my public learning log. It documents the test cases, bug reports, and exercises I complete while building practical QA skills.
